text: PT Aplikasi Karya Anak Bangsa (most commonly known as Gojek) is a Jakarta based on-demand service platform. It also does digital payments. Gojek was started in Indonesia in 2009 as a call center. It connects consumers to courier delivery and two-wheeled ride-hailing services. Gojek launched its application in 2015 with only four services: GoRide, GoSend, GoShop, and GoFood. It raised over $1 billion 2019 and is now valued at US$10 billion. Gojek has turned into a Super App. It now provides more than 20 services. == References == Category:Indonesia Category:Technology companies of Asia
title: Gojek
